      <bioghist id="aspace_9ad70efaa27be13365d97a115d6c0136">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Theodor Reik: associate of Sigmund Freud, University of Vienna, 1910-1938; lecturer in Vienna, Berlin, The Hague, New York, 1912-1944; director, Society for Psychoanalytic Psychology, N.Y., 1941-1970; professor of psychology, Adelphi University; author of many books.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d15527bde930d38b4f7af9cfe5443924">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Principally the typescript draft for Theodor Reik's book, Listening with the Third Ear (1947). Also included are two chapters in manuscript form. In addition there is a letter to his publisher, John Farrar, with a copy of an article "The original 'Sleeping Beauty' discovered," which appears to be a literary hoax.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_3f50c64126bb1e9c015c13c35c976060">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The collection is open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
